# cursor-only: full ci verification

These expectations apply to Cursor agents in this repo. They are intentionally **not** duplicated in `CLAUDE.md` or `.claude/` so other tooling and maintainers are not nudged toward a full `make ci` on every change.

## before committing

Run `make ci` before committing when your changes touch application code, tests, or build config.

## before reporting work complete

Tooling can report success even when the tree does not pass CI. Do not report a coding task as complete until you have run `make ci` (or the project's equivalent) and fixed all errors it reports.
